<Layout title='Plasterers & Painters in Windsor | Hancock' description='Plastering and painting in Windsor. Fixed-price quotes from City & Guilds certified contractors covering Windsor and the surrounding area.' activePage='areas'>
<section style="position:relative;height:420px;display:flex;align-items:flex-end;">
  <div style="position:absolute;top:0;left:0;right:0;bottom:0;background-image:url('/uploads/Hancock-plastering-and-painting%20(4).webp');background-size:cover;background-position:center 40%;"></div>
  <div style="position:absolute;top:0;left:0;right:0;bottom:0;background:linear-gradient(to top,rgba(15,23,42,0.92) 0%,rgba(15,23,42,0.5) 55%,rgba(15,23,42,0.18) 100%);"></div>
  <div style="position:relative;z-index:1;max-width:1280px;margin:0 auto;padding:0 24px 56px;width:100%;box-sizing:border-box;">
    <p style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:12px;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.55);margin:0 0 12px;"><a href="/" style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.55);text-decoration:none;">Home</a> / <a href="/areas" style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.55);text-decoration:none;">Areas</a> / Windsor</p>
    <h1 style="font-family:'Lexend',sans-serif;font-size:clamp(34px,5vw,58px);font-weight:700;color:#ffffff;margin:0 0 12px;letter-spacing:-0.04em;line-height:1.05;">Plasterer in Windsor</h1>
    <p style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:17px;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.75);margin:0;max-width:500px;">SL4 · Venetian plastering, sash window painting, and high-end finishing for Windsor's period properties.</p>
  </div>
</section>
<section style="padding:64px 24px;background:#ffffff;border-bottom:1px solid #E2E8F0;">
  <div style="max-width:1280px;margin:0 auto;display:flex;gap:64px;flex-wrap:wrap;">
    <div style="flex:2;min-width:280px;">
      <p style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:12px;font-weight:600;color:#0C7BA8;letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;margin:0 0 12px;">About this area</p>
      <h2 style="font-family:'Lexend',sans-serif;font-size:clamp(22px,3vw,32px);font-weight:600;color:#0F172A;margin:0 0 20px;letter-spacing:-0.03em;line-height:1.2;">Windsor has one of the highest concentrations of conservation area and period property in our coverage zone.</h2>
      <p style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:16px;color:#334155;line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 16px;">Windsor's Georgian and Victorian town centre properties — particularly around the Castle, Park Street, and Sheet Street — carry conservation area designations that affect permitted external finishes. Lime-compatible materials are often required on the oldest properties. Original cornicing, sash windows, and period plaster features are the norm in these streets.</p>
      <p style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:16px;color:#334155;line-height:1.75;margin:0;">The Clewer and Dedworth areas bring modern executive housing alongside established residential streets. Venetian plastering enquiries are consistent from Windsor — it's the natural finish choice for a high-end interior in a period building.</p>
    </div>
    <div style="flex:1;min-width:220px;">
      <div style="background:#F8FAFC;border:1px solid #E2E8F0;border-radius:8px;padding:24px;">
        <p style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;color:#64748B;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.08em;margin:0 0 16px;">Area facts</p>
        <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:10px;">
          <div style="display:flex;justify-content:space-between;border-bottom:1px solid #E2E8F0;padding-bottom:10px;"><span style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:13px;color:#64748B;">Postcode</span><span style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-weight:600;color:#0F172A;">SL4</span></div>
          <div style="display:flex;justify-content:space-between;border-bottom:1px solid #E2E8F0;padding-bottom:10px;"><span style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:13px;color:#64748B;">Dominant era</span><span style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-weight:600;color:#0F172A;">Georgian / Victorian</span></div>
          <div style="display:flex;justify-content:space-between;"><span style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:13px;color:#64748B;">Conservation area</span><span style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-weight:600;color:#0F172A;">Yes — central</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
<section style="padding:64px 24px;background:#ffffff;border-bottom:1px solid #E2E8F0;">
  <div style="max-width:1280px;margin:0 auto;display:flex;gap:64px;flex-wrap:wrap;">
    <div style="flex:1;min-width:300px;">
      <p style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:12px;font-weight:600;color:#0C7BA8;letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;margin:0 0 12px;">Neighbourhoods we work in</p>
      <h2 style="font-family:'Lexend',sans-serif;font-size:clamp(20px,3vw,30px);font-weight:600;color:#0F172A;margin:0 0 20px;letter-spacing:-0.03em;line-height:1.2;">A royal town built around period property and conservation.</h2>
      <p style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:16px;color:#334155;line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 16px;">Windsor's centre is dominated by Georgian and Victorian townhouses, much of it within conservation areas in the shadow of the Castle. This is genuine period fabric — solid-brick construction, lime plaster behind later skims, original sash windows, cornicing and ceiling detail worth preserving. Work here has to be done sympathetically, with the right materials for the wall, not just whatever's quickest.</p>
      <p style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:16px;color:#334155;line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 16px;"><strong>Clewer and Dedworth</strong> to the west bring 20th-century and postwar residential into the mix — more conventional cavity-wall stock with rendered and painted elevations. <strong>Old Windsor</strong> and the riverside roads add high-value detached housing, while modern apartment developments have appeared around the town centre.</p>
      <p style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:16px;color:#334155;line-height:1.75;margin:0;">The period stock is what sets Windsor apart from our suburban areas — and it's why Venetian plastering, sash window painting, and careful traditional repair work feature so heavily in what we're asked to do here.</p>
    </div>
    <div style="flex:1;min-width:300px;">
      <p style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:12px;font-weight:600;color:#0C7BA8;letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;margin:0 0 12px;">What homeowners ask for</p>
      <h2 style="font-family:'Lexend',sans-serif;font-size:clamp(20px,3vw,30px);font-weight:600;color:#0F172A;margin:0 0 20px;letter-spacing:-0.03em;line-height:1.2;">Period-sensitive finishes done properly.</h2>
      <p style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:16px;color:#334155;line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 16px;">Windsor enquiries lean toward the higher-specification end: polished Venetian plaster in hallways and principal rooms, careful repair of original lime plaster and cornicing, sash window overhaul and repainting, and quality interior decorating in homes where the finish is expected to match the address. On conservation properties, getting the right breathable materials onto a solid wall is not optional — modern gypsum and plastic paint trap moisture and cause more harm than good.</p>
      <p style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:16px;color:#334155;line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 16px;">Exterior masonry and render painting on the Clewer and Dedworth stock we schedule for the drier months. Sash window work — strip, repair, prime, and finish — is a year-round speciality.</p>
      <p style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:16px;color:#334155;line-height:1.75;margin:0;">Clients here want it right, want it discreet, and want a clear fixed price before anyone picks up a tool. That's how we operate.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
<section style="padding:56px 24px;background:#ffffff;border-bottom:1px solid #E2E8F0;">
  <div style="max-width:1280px;margin:0 auto;">
    <p style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:12px;font-weight:600;color:#0C7BA8;letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;margin:0 0 24px;">Working in Windsor</p>
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(220px,1fr));gap:20px;">
      <div>
        <h3 style="font-family:'Lexend',sans-serif;font-size:16px;font-weight:600;color:#0F172A;margin:0 0 8px;">~35 minutes from base</h3>
        <p style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:14px;color:#334155;line-height:1.65;margin:0;">A clear run from Harefield via the M25 and M4. Windsor is a planned area rather than a daily one — we schedule jobs efficiently and quote honestly on access and timing.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 style="font-family:'Lexend',sans-serif;font-size:16px;font-weight:600;color:#0F172A;margin:0 0 8px;">Conservation-aware</h3>
        <p style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:14px;color:#334155;line-height:1.65;margin:0;">We know listed and conservation-area properties carry restrictions on finishes. We work with breathable, period-appropriate materials and advise on what's suitable before quoting.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 style="font-family:'Lexend',sans-serif;font-size:16px;font-weight:600;color:#0F172A;margin:0 0 8px;">Access &amp; parking</h3>
        <p style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:14px;color:#334155;line-height:1.65;margin:0;">Town-centre period streets often have permit parking and narrow access — we plan loading and materials around it so there's no disruption to you or your neighbours.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 style="font-family:'Lexend',sans-serif;font-size:16px;font-weight:600;color:#0F172A;margin:0 0 8px;">Clean, tidy, insured</h3>
        <p style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:14px;color:#334155;line-height:1.65;margin:0;">Original features protected, surfaces covered, site left immaculate. Fully insured, City &amp; Guilds qualified, no subcontractors on your property.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
<section style="padding:0;">
  <div style="position:relative;height:clamp(300px,42vw,440px);">
